+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772766089813,"sessionID":"ses_33ee852e0ffejbvyovPis5KfIx","part":{"id":"prt_cc117d09d001PL4UhvdiMwAh3t","sessionID":"ses_33ee852e0ffejbvyovPis5KfIx","messageID":"msg_cc117cf4c002IL1leHw20kYiZ3","type":"tool","callID":"a5e42de95","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\nOriginal Request:\nBuild a collaborative real-time document editing server with REST API for documents, version history, WebSocket real-time collaboration using OT, persistence via SQLite (better-sqlite3). Export `createApp` from `src/server.ts` returning {app, start, stop}. Ensure build, lint, tests pass.\n\nUser Clarifications:\nNone yet.\n\nGoal:\n- `npm run build` compiles without errors.\n- `npm run lint` passes.\n- Server supports CRUD via REST, version retrieval, and WebSocket collaborative editing with conflict resolution.\n- Persistence across restarts.\n- Handles at least 10 concurrent clients.\n- Proper error handling.\n- Integration tests verify functionality.\n\nApproach:\n1. Create project structure (`src/`, ensure tsconfig includes src). Already present.\n2. Implement SQLite schema (documents, versions) – use better-sqlite3. Provide helper functions.\n3. Implement REST API endpoints for CRUD and version history using Express.\n4. Implement simple OT algorithm for insert/delete operations.\n5. Add WebSocket server (ws) handling connections per document, syncing state, applying operations, broadcasting.\n6. Ensure versioning and conflict resolution – simple version check; if mismatch, reject (could be extended later).\n7. Write integration tests using supertest for REST and ws client for collaborative edits.\n8. Add scripts in package.json if missing (build, lint, test already exist).\n9. Update ESLint config if needed.\n10. Ensure graceful shutdown releasing DB and sockets.\n\nKey Files:\n- src/server.ts (main implementation, already created).\n- src/types.ts (optional for operation types).\n- tests/ (add integration tests).\n- schema.sql (existing, but server creates tables if missing).\n\nRisks:\n- OT algorithm simplistic – may reject concurrent edits, but requirement only to preserve both insertions, not full transformation.\n- Version mismatch handling – send error, client may need to resync.\n- WebSocket path parsing – ensure correct document id extraction.\n- Database concurrency – better-sqlite3 is synchronous, should be fine for low concurrency.\n- Clean shutdown of WebSocket server and DB.\n\nNext Steps:\n- Write integration tests.\n- Add any missing npm scripts.\n- Run lint/build/tests.\n- Update README if needed.\n---\n","encoding":"utf-8"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772766089807,"end":1772766089812}}}}
